wiki.content: “That’s What Love Is” is the fifteenth song on Justin Bieber’s fifth studio album "Changes". On the track, Bieber sings with a backing guitar instrumental about how much he admires the “greatness” that comes with being in a relationship, and how he has learned from being in love. In a Pitchfork review of "Changes", Jayson Greene called this song a highlight of the album: “That’s What Love Is” features nothing but an acoustic guitar, capo’d high and twinkling like a music box. The words redefine “sweet nothings” (“Don’t nobody else deserve my eyes,” he avows) but they dissolve in the sunlight of Bieber’s falsetto. The way he capers between chest and head voice is effortless and dazzling, like watching a figure skater land triple lutzes, one after the other. For exactly two minutes and forty-five seconds, the joy he takes in his talent is palpable. Read more on Last.fm.
